    dc:creator "Kovačić, Marcelo; Sadeghi, Reza; Esmaeili, Hamid Reza" ;
    dc:date "2020" ;
    dc:title "New species of Silhouettea (Teleostei: Gobiidae) from Qeshm Island, Iran and the DNA barcoding of the Persian Gulf and Oman Sea gobies" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702835>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702833>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702837>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702839>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702841>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702843>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702845> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702835>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Silhouettea ghazalae sp. nov., PMR VP4678, holotype, female, 27.35 + 6.29 mm, Qeshm Island, Persian Gulf. A: freshly collected specimen; B: preserved specimen. Photos by R. Sadeghi (A), M. Kovačić (B)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3702835/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702833>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Silhouettea ghazalae sp. nov., PMR VP4678, reversible stained holotype, female, 27.35 + 6.29 mm, Qeshm Island, Persian Gulf: A: chin with mental fold outlined, head down position; B: membranous edge at opercle, extension on the pectoral rays origin marked; C: preopercular edge, head sensory papillae rows resembling longitudinally dashed lines (e.g. row c) or transversal stiches (e.g. row ot). D: membranous edge at ventrolateral head ridge (vhr) divided from opercular membrane (om) by indentation (marked by arrow); E: nape and predorsal region naked; Photos by M. Kovačić." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3702833/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702837>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Silhouettea ghazalae sp. nov. Head lateral line sensory papillae and canal pores: PMR VP4678, holotype, female, 27.35 + 6.29 mm, Qeshm Island, Persian Gulf. Terminology in text. Drawing by M. Kovačić." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3702837/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702839>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Silhouettea ghazalae sp. nov., PMR VP4678, holotype, Qeshm Island, Persian Gulf. Nape and predorsal region with median white spot marked: A: freshly collected specimen; B: preserved specimen. Photos by R. Sadeghi (A), M. Kovačić (B)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3702839/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702841>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Silhouettea ghazalae sp. nov., PMR VP4678, holotype, female, 27.35 + 6.29 mm, Qeshm Island, Persian Gulf: A: whole lateral view with the vertebrae numbered; B) close-up image of the caudal fin skeleton: EPU=epural, HS PU=haemal spine of preural centrum, HYP=hypural, NS PU=neural spine of preural, centrum, PHY=parhypural, PU=preural centrum, UR=urostyle, DPR, dorsal procurrent rays; VPR, ventral procurrent rays. X-ray by H.R. Esmaeili and U.K. Schliewen." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3702841/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702843>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Intertidal coast of Qeshm Island, Iran, type locality of Silhouettea ghazalae. Photo by R. Sadeghi." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3702843/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702845>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Bayesian tree visualizing the results of the three different molecular species delimitation methods based on COI. ABGD: Automatic Barcode Gap Discovery; SP: reversed Statistical Parsimony; and bPTP: Bayesian Poisson tree process model. Posterior probability values are provided at the nodes." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3702845/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

